description:
This is a very unprofessional release by MRO.
We are not really a ripping group.
We are mainly a distro channel that distrubutes other groups&amp;#039; releases.
However, due to the poor sounding of these demos,
I could not bare to see Chris Cornell and Rage
Against the Machine receive this kind of audio
treatment.  I brought upon myself the mission
at hand to make these things sound halfway decent.
I will admit I am not an audio engineer, but you
have to admit my &quot;audio facelift&quot; has made these demos sound bettter.
Before I touched these recordings, they sounded too soft.
I hope I did a good job and that all of you out there reading
this will agree.  I used Cool Edit Pro 2 to fix these tracks.
Enjoy!  I got the original tracks from iDX.  Props to them releasing the tracks
first to the scene.  I just made them better.

Props to the inner and neg crew.  I love you all.  Thanks for all your support.

P.S.  Track 13 has clicks.  That&amp;#039;s not me.  That&amp;#039;s from the originals.  I did
not cause that.  I just made the tracks sound louder.  You can compare the
originals at http://spazioweb.inwind.it/chriscornelldemo/

